Use this add-on [1] or the userContent.css file in Firefox.
Thats what it looks like:  http://oi44.tinypic.com/2je5usy.jpg<p><pre><code>    @-moz-document url-prefix(https://news.ycombinator.com/) {
    td { vertical-align: top }
    td > img { background: repeating-linear-gradient(to right, rgba(0,0,0,0), rgba(0,0,0,0) 38px, rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 38px, rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 40px); margin-top: 4px; height: 10px !important; }
    }
</code></pre>
[1] https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/generic-css-loader-2/
